title: Compiler panic: evaluating trait selection obligation

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code I don't have a minimal reproducer at hand unfortunately, and cannot share our proprietary code base with you. Sorry. The project uses `sqlx` with a postgres database that has just freshly been migrated, if that is of any relevance. I cannot reproduce the bug after `cargo clean`, so this is possibly a poisoned / corrupted cache. (Still reporting this since `rustc` has asked me to) ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.65.0 (897e37553 2022-11-02) ``` ### Error output ``` warning: build failed, waiting for other jobs to finish... thread 'rustc' panicked at 'Failed to extract DefId: local_def_id_to_hir_id c869a85bf893cd50-df66789a2c5c4d83', compiler/rustc_middle/src/dep_graph/dep_node.rs:267:17 error: internal compiler error: unexpected panic note: the compiler unexpectedly panicked. this is a bug. note: we would appreciate a bug report: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/new?labels=C-bug%2C+I-ICE%2C+T-compiler&template=ice.md note: rustc 1.65.0 (897e37553 2022-11-02) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib -C embed-bitcode=no -C incremental=[REDACTED] -C link-arg=-fuse-ld=lld -C force-frame-pointers=yes -C link-arg=-Wl,--compress-debug-sections=zlib,--no-rosegment note: some of the compiler flags provided by cargo are hidden query stack during panic: #0 [evaluate_obligation] evaluating trait selection obligation `some_lib::Control: core::marker::Send` #1 [codegen_select_candidate] computing candidate for `>> as core::ops::unsize::CoerceUnsized, tonic::status::Status>> + core::marker::Send>>>>` #2 [collect_and_partition_mono_items] collect_and_partition_mono_items #3 [exported_symbols] exported_symbols end of query stack ```
